Sometime atypical input will cause our regular-expression-based
link extractors to exceed recursion limits, causing this error.

I can reproduce the error crawling just this one URL.

I made a bug at Sourceforge to track this issue:

   [ 1122839 ] StackOverflowError in ExtractorHTML
   http://sourceforge.net/tracker/index.php?func=detail&aid=1122839&group_id=73833&atid=539099

However, another recent change in HEAD, which will be available in the
1.4 release in March, makes it possible for the crawl to continue after
hitting such an error...

   [ 1093073 ] StackOverflowError shouldn&#39;t kill crawl
   http://sourceforge.net/tracker/index.php?func=detail&aid=1093073&group_id=73833&atid=539099

So, actually preventing this error from happening by changing the
ExtractorHTML&#39;s approach (fixing the new bug #1122839) may not be
tackled soon -- at least not until after some new HTML extraction
techniques are tried out.

Though this error will no longer kill the crawl, it will spoil the URL
in progress -- cancelling its processing, and NOT storing it to an ARC.
I&#39;ve also created an issue to fix this:

   [ 1122836 ] Localize StackOverflowError in Extractors
   http://sourceforge.net/tracker/index.php?func=detail&aid=1122836&group_id=73833&atid=539099

- Gordon @ IA

